ls                                    macro                                   ls

NAME
     llss - UNIX file listing

SYNOPSIS

     llss [[ooppttiioonnss]] [[ffiilleess ...... ]]

DESCRIPTION

     The llss macro executes the UNIX command llss in the current directory.  Some
     of the more useful options to llss are:

     --tt Sort by last-modification time.

     --uu Sort by last-access time.

     --rr Reverse the sort order.

     --RR Recursively descend directories and list.

DEFINITION

     ddeeff llss ''uunniixx((""llss $$**""))''

EXAMPLE

     llss --ttrr ddoo..**

